The scp task doesnot handle ipv6 ip as hostname. The problem is in Scp class. The method parseUri is wrongly extracting the ip address based on first appearance of ":" after @ . But in IPv6 it is having more than one ":" in the ip address.

Example 

For ip fd01:0:101:2608:0:11ff:fe42:e13c the scp task gets the hostname as fd01 as the host name is parsed based on the index of ":" after "@". It should use lastIndexOf the ":" uri to get the proper hostname to support ipv6

The current implementation is :

 int indexOfPath = uri.indexOf(':', indexOfAt + 1);
        if(indexOfPath == -1)
        {
            throw new BuildException((new StringBuilder()).append("no remote path in ").append(uri).toString());
        }
        setHost(uri.substring(indexOfAt + 1, indexOfPath));


The fix for bug :

int indexOfPath = uri.lastIndexOf(':');
     if (indexOfPath == -1) {
       throw new BuildException("no remote path in " + uri);
   }

   setHost(uri.substring(indexOfAt + 1, indexOfPath));
